			<ns0:name>pquir...@gmail.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108874970534447385653/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Allow NaCl to read/write from Google Drive files that are synced locally on the users system.  This would require some sort of integration between Google Chrome and Google Drive apps.
Of course Chrome would have to ask the user for permission.
Building webapps that integrate with Google Drive is difficult but this would make it more possible.

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Currently not possible.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
Difficult to build apps that integrate with Google Drive.
I've tried to use Google Apps Scripts but the DocsList API is too buggy and is not usable.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Allow NaCl to read/write Google Drive files on users local system if they are running Google Drive app.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
Awesome websites, like video editors, better image editors, etc. that work with Google Drive files.

